ST Engineering-NTU Corporate Lab invites applications for the position of Project Officer.
Key Responsibilities:

  Anti-disturbance control algorithm for UAV operating in environment with harsh wind
  Control algorithm development for UAV to handle load variation
  Simulation study
  Implement the algorithms using C++ and ROS to work out a reliable solution
  Evaluate the algorithms through flight tests

Job Requirements:

  Bachelor's degree in Electrical and Electronic Engineering
  Strong background in control theory
  Experiences in control system design including anti-disturbance control
  Good publication record in control
  Familiar with C++
  Good communication skill

We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.